President Donald J. Trump spoke with Prime Minister Haider al-Abadi of Iraq to express the support of the United States in the fight against ISIS. Trump emphasized the strengthening of the US military and praised Iraqi forces for their progress in Mosul. He also offered condolences for the loss of Iraqi lives in the counter-ISIS campaign. The leaders discussed the strong partnership between the Iraqi and US militaries and the threat posed by Iran in the region. They reaffirmed their commitment to the long-term partnership between the US and Iraq based on the U.S.-Iraq Strategic Framework Agreement.